  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Starting state&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    These instructions are based on the assumption that you are familiar with creating work items. See &lt;a&#xD;
    href=&quot;http://pic.dhe.ibm.com/infocenter/clmhelp/v4r0/topic/com.ibm.team.workitem.doc/topics/t_creating_work_items.html&quot;&#xD;
    target=&quot;_blank&quot;>Creating work items&lt;/a> and &lt;a&#xD;
    href=&quot;http://pic.dhe.ibm.com/infocenter/clmhelp/v4r0/topic/com.ibm.team.workitem.doc/topics/t_creating_work_items_web.html&quot;&#xD;
     target=&quot;_blank&quot;>Creating work items in the web client&lt;/a> for more information.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Steps&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This task covers the following steps:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Use a work item of Task type to capture a work package description, documenting the details of the work package in&#xD;
        the task fields. &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Note that tasks are first added to the backlog, which is identified in the Filed Against field. When they&#xD;
                are ready for implementation, tasks should be moved to a Sprint Backlog or Iteration Plan in the Planned&#xD;
                For field.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Create a child work item describing a task that is performed as part of this work package. &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Create as many child work items (tasks) as required to complete the work described in the top level work&#xD;
                package.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Result&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    A work package is created that consists of a parent work item, and the child work items that must be completed in order&#xD;
    to deliver the work package.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription>
